SIMPLE: subscript
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subscript
<hw>Sub"script</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subscriptus</ets>, p. p. See <er>Subscribe</er>.]</ety>
<def>Written below or underneath; <as>as, iota <ex>subscript</ex></as>.
(See under <er>Iota</er>.) Specifically <fld>(Math.)</fld>, said of
marks, figures, or letters (suffixes), written below and usually to the
right of other letters to distinguish them; <as>as, <it>a</it>,
<it>n</it>, 2, in the symbols <ex>X<subs>a</subs></ex>,
<ex>A<subs>n</subs></ex>, <ex>Y<subs>2</subs></ex></as>. See
<er>Suffix</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2, and <er>Subindex</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subscript</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subscript
<hw>Sub"script</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything written below.</def>
<rj><au>Bentley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subscription</ent>⟦br⟧
